# Cursor rules

Read `AGENTS.md` in the repo root for full project context — it is the single source of truth
(architecture, Xero API facts, conventions, status).

Critical:
- Xero Projects REST API for time entries (no MCP covers Projects). `POST /Projects/{id}/Time`:
  userId, taskId, dateUtc, duration in MINUTES.
- One org connection + Teams-user→{xeroUserId, allowedProjectIds} map; no per-user OAuth.
- Grounding validates LLM output against the allowed list; never invent project/task or guess
  duration — flag instead.
- Secrets only in .env (git-ignored); never in .env.example.
